1
00:00:07,326 --> 00:00:10,459
(Previously)
Hey, kiddo. My husband is taking me out.

2
00:00:16,232 --> 00:00:17,761
Erng, let's meet up.

3
00:00:18,533 --> 00:00:19,533
Surprise!

4
00:00:20,066 --> 00:00:21,466
Surprised, you bastard?

5
00:00:21,900 --> 00:00:23,220
What the hell are you doing here?

6
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:25,533
Because you messed with my wife first.

7
00:00:25,933 --> 00:00:27,066
You think I'm scared of you?

8
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:28,400
P'Bom.

9
00:00:29,466 --> 00:00:30,466
Damn it!

10
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Where are you?

11
00:00:34,566 --> 00:00:36,066
Something that's easily stolen

12
00:00:36,366 --> 00:00:38,266
can easily be taken away from you too.

13
00:00:39,700 --> 00:00:42,166
Do you want to sleep at home
or in the hospital like Bom?

14
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:44,200
Home.

15
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:46,700
You're screwed!

16
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:48,500
Erng is in beast mode.

17
00:00:50,966 --> 00:00:52,733
Nok is asking what on earth just happened.

18
00:01:11,533 --> 00:01:12,733
Don't touch me.

19
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:16,566
Erng, please don't be mad at me.

20
00:01:18,933 --> 00:01:21,133
Lying violates the fourth precept.

21
00:01:23,966 --> 00:01:26,400
Now that you're mad at me

22
00:01:27,466 --> 00:01:28,933
my heart is completely broken.

23
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:30,500
Ouch!

24
00:01:30,866 --> 00:01:32,600
Go find a way to punish yourself.

25
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:33,800
Nibble on you?

26
00:01:35,533 --> 00:01:37,133
Is that a good punishment?

27
00:01:38,866 --> 00:01:40,066
That's a win for you, Hia.

28
00:01:41,166 --> 00:01:42,266
Now I'm sad.

29
00:01:42,700 --> 00:01:43,980
You always see right through me.

30
00:01:49,500 --> 00:01:52,484
Actually, I wasn't even
mad by the time we got home.

31
00:01:52,485 --> 00:01:54,038
But can you promise me one thing?

32
00:01:54,039 --> 00:01:57,933
Just tell me the truth. I won't be
mad if you have a good reason.

33
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:01,408
Saying that...

34
00:02:02,714 --> 00:02:04,319
means you're still mad.

35
00:02:06,391 --> 00:02:08,222
I need to hug

36
00:02:08,763 --> 00:02:09,763
and pamper you

37
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:11,725
to make you feel better.

38
00:02:12,941 --> 00:02:14,281
Hia.

39
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,966
Don't sit on me. The chair might break.

40
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:17,200
It won't break.

41
00:02:17,933 --> 00:02:20,413
I'll turn it into a fun chair.
(the kind of chair used for sex)

42
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:22,776
You're not actually trying to
make it up to me, are you?

43
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:23,800
Of course I am.

44
00:02:27,133 --> 00:02:28,133
Yeah, right.

45
00:02:28,533 --> 00:02:29,813
Come give me a kiss on the head.

46
00:02:29,966 --> 00:02:31,321
The spicy salad had
fermented fish in it.

47
00:02:31,322 --> 00:02:33,166
My breath stinks right now, you know?

48
00:02:33,466 --> 00:02:34,956
So you won't let me nibble on you?

49
00:02:34,957 --> 00:02:35,500
Yep.

50
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:36,200
Oops!

51
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:37,200
No nibbling.

52
00:02:37,666 --> 00:02:38,666
Get off me now.

53
00:02:40,066 --> 00:02:41,300
You're so cruel, babe.

54
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:44,700
You lied, so no nibbling for you.

55
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:47,600
But I kept the first, second,
third, and fifth precepts.

56
00:02:47,866 --> 00:02:49,300
Did you skip the fourth on purpose?

57
00:02:49,933 --> 00:02:52,500
Lord of Death, I don't know this man.

58
00:02:54,066 --> 00:02:57,700
Be my wife today, and
get a free ticket to hell.

59
00:02:57,933 --> 00:02:59,600
So you know you're a sinner.

60
00:02:59,966 --> 00:03:03,500
I know, but I'm trying to
make merit to offset it.

61
00:03:12,933 --> 00:03:13,933
Hia.

62
00:03:15,666 --> 00:03:18,466
I've made a list of things
we need to order and buy.

63
00:03:18,933 --> 00:03:20,933
Come take a look and see if
we should cut anything.

64
00:03:23,266 --> 00:03:24,566
You can make the decision.

65
00:03:25,366 --> 00:03:27,166
I don't know what we need or how much.

66
00:03:27,533 --> 00:03:29,866
But the one paying still
needs to check the list.

67
00:03:40,366 --> 00:03:41,533
Just go with this.

68
00:03:42,933 --> 00:03:43,933
What about these?

69
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:45,866
Do we have to buy these ourselves?

70
00:03:46,733 --> 00:03:47,533
Yes.

71
00:03:47,643 --> 00:03:50,266
We can take my car to pick
them up tomorrow morning.

72
00:03:52,266 --> 00:03:53,266
Okay.

73
00:03:57,366 --> 00:03:59,133
Your bangs are getting long, Hia.

74
00:03:59,700 --> 00:04:00,933
I'll get them cut later.

75
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:02,900
They're not even that long.

76
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,000
Just a little bit.

77
00:04:04,266 --> 00:04:05,386
Want me to cut them for you?

78
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:06,866
It's just your bangs.

79
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:08,500
No way.

80
00:04:08,766 --> 00:04:10,086
Do you even know how to cut hair?

81
00:04:10,300 --> 00:04:11,300
Hey!

82
00:04:11,533 --> 00:04:13,900
I took a hair-cutting course
before opening the bar.

83
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:16,000
I still have the scissors under the table.

84
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:17,466
Are you bluffing?

85
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:18,800
I cut my own hair too.

86
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:20,700
I'm just too lazy to go to a salon.

87
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:24,100
Come here.

88
00:04:25,266 --> 00:04:26,266
Sit properly.

89
00:04:26,866 --> 00:04:28,366
Just trim a little bit off.

90
00:04:30,866 --> 00:04:32,000
Are you serious about this?

91
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,000
Hey!

92
00:04:37,133 --> 00:04:38,133
Come on.

93
00:04:43,533 --> 00:04:44,533
Sit still, Hia.

94
00:04:49,966 --> 00:04:50,766
Just a little bit, okay?

95
00:04:50,766 --> 00:04:51,766
Yeah.

96
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,000
Is it uneven?

97
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:06,100
Calm down.

98
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:07,200
Do you have a mirror?

99
00:05:07,666 --> 00:05:09,066
Sit still. Don't move.

100
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:12,600
Wait.

101
00:05:12,700 --> 00:05:14,133
Let me style it properly.

102
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,000
Hold on.

103
00:05:17,411 --> 00:05:19,066
Can you cut it into curved bangs?

104
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:21,166
Just get a normal haircut
like a regular person.

105
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:22,733
But then it won't stand out.

106
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,101
What a reason.

107
00:05:24,102 --> 00:05:25,102
Can you do it?

108
00:05:27,533 --> 00:05:29,266
It's really just a tiny bit.

109
00:05:29,933 --> 00:05:32,200
It's basically the same style.
No difference at all.

110
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:34,933
Don't be dramatic, Hia.

111
00:05:37,966 --> 00:05:38,966
Fine.

112
00:05:39,266 --> 00:05:40,800
Then give me the 'Mother' style.

113
00:05:42,966 --> 00:05:43,966
What 'Mother' style?

114
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:47,142
Mother. [Sounds like "micro-bangs" in Thai]

115
00:05:47,166 --> 00:05:48,900
Are you serious about anything at all?

116
00:05:49,766 --> 00:05:51,666
Even with uneven hair, you're still joking.

117
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,776
Actually, there is one
thing I'm serious about.

118
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:54,800
What is it?

119
00:05:56,333 --> 00:05:57,893
I'm afraid my wife will stop loving me.

120
00:05:59,066 --> 00:06:01,133
Then you have nothing
to worry about in this life.

121
00:06:06,766 --> 00:06:07,766
Oh!

122
00:06:07,933 --> 00:06:09,493
Are we getting this haircut done today?

123
00:06:11,933 --> 00:06:12,966
Make me look handsome.

124
00:06:14,166 --> 00:06:15,166
You're already handsome.

125
00:06:16,390 --> 00:06:17,410
Bibi (baby in Thai)

126
00:06:18,466 --> 00:06:19,466
Give me a kiss.

127
00:06:27,466 --> 00:06:29,395
Do you kiss other barbers too?

128
00:06:30,251 --> 00:06:31,629
Don't let me find out.

129
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,166
You cut the hair on top,

130
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:38,880
can you also cut the hair "down there" too?

131
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:40,733
I'll snip it right off.

132
00:06:48,566 --> 00:06:49,566
Go ahead and cut it.

133
00:06:51,133 --> 00:06:52,400
I'd love to get it cut.

134
00:07:00,166 --> 00:07:01,733
Aren't you a bit too much to handle?

135
00:07:02,366 --> 00:07:03,366
Shall we go?

136
00:07:54,300 --> 00:08:02,300
"ChermChey"
(Episode 6)

137
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:13,800
It looks even to me.

138
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:15,640
If you hadn't messed up...

139
00:08:16,733 --> 00:08:18,333
it would have been the exact same style.

140
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,933
And who kept playing
around, causing the mistake?

141
00:08:26,166 --> 00:08:27,166
That would be me.

142
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,200
Erng did nothing wrong.

143
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:31,300
You're never wrong, babe.

144
00:08:32,866 --> 00:08:34,386
This style actually looks good on you.

145
00:08:35,166 --> 00:08:37,566
Very 'Mother Mother' handsome.

146
00:08:39,466 --> 00:08:41,666
They say eyebrows like yours
mean you're such a playboy.

147
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:46,874
Really?

148
00:08:46,874 --> 00:08:47,602
Ouch!

149
00:08:47,603 --> 00:08:49,476
Right now, I love my
wife more than anything.

150
00:08:49,477 --> 00:08:50,403
Is that so?

151
00:08:50,403 --> 00:08:51,403
Of course.

152
00:08:56,180 --> 00:08:57,180
Hia.

153
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:04,500
Stop for a second.

154
00:09:08,133 --> 00:09:09,133
What's up?

155
00:09:10,566 --> 00:09:12,133
Tomorrow, before we go shopping...

156
00:09:12,933 --> 00:09:14,533
I want to drop by and see Bom.

157
00:09:27,266 --> 00:09:29,300
Why do you have to bring
him up and ruin my mood?

158
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:32,040
If I get mad, I might get rough with you.

159
00:09:32,133 --> 00:09:33,213
Then you'll complain again.

160
00:09:34,333 --> 00:09:35,866
Hia, let me finish first.

161
00:09:40,733 --> 00:09:41,733
Go on.

162
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:43,900
I'm going to collect a debt.

163
00:09:45,466 --> 00:09:46,800
And you're coming with me.

164
00:09:48,733 --> 00:09:50,300
Do you think Bom will pay you back?

165
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:52,800
I don't know.

166
00:09:53,066 --> 00:09:55,000
But my dad's money is in there too.

167
00:09:56,866 --> 00:09:58,533
I just want that part back.

168
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:05,466
Want me to collect it for you?

169
00:10:07,266 --> 00:10:08,266
How?

170
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:10,700
By force.

171
00:10:11,533 --> 00:10:13,600
He's already half-dead as it is.

172
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:17,333
Bom won't die that easily.

173
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:21,520
But the one who's about to die right now...

174
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:23,300
is you.

175
00:10:25,933 --> 00:10:28,700
Now I'm really starting to feel scared.

176
00:10:32,300 --> 00:10:33,966
Oh, Hia!

177
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:35,973
You're definitely getting
what you wished for.

178
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,766
- Hia.
- What's wrong, babe?

179
00:10:43,766 --> 00:10:44,766
Ouch!

180
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,000
Stop it.

181
00:10:47,866 --> 00:10:49,466
You can bite me as hard as you want.

182
00:10:51,994 --> 00:10:52,769
Hia!

183
00:10:52,769 --> 00:10:53,769
Where are you going?

184
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,166
My cheeks are all bruised now.

185
00:10:56,266 --> 00:10:57,466
Let's bruise them some more.

186
00:10:58,166 --> 00:10:59,834
Or something else
might get bruised instead.

187
00:10:59,835 --> 00:11:00,835
Oh, really?

188
00:11:07,266 --> 00:11:08,266
My little baby.

189
00:11:08,473 --> 00:11:09,753
Should I throw you onto the bed?

190
00:11:10,764 --> 00:11:11,764
Get off me.

191
00:11:11,915 --> 00:11:12,969
No, I won't.

192
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:25,400
My wife...

193
00:11:26,366 --> 00:11:27,766
shifting gears like crazy...

194
00:11:27,966 --> 00:11:29,533
like a drug-running mobster.

195
00:11:30,866 --> 00:11:31,966
If you weren't my wife...

196
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:33,940
anyone would think
you're a total mob boss.

197
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,200
Hia.

198
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:39,900
When I go inside...

199
00:11:40,466 --> 00:11:41,933
you can come in with me.

200
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:44,666
So you can be sure I'm not hiding anything.

201
00:11:45,766 --> 00:11:46,800
I'll definitely be there.

202
00:11:47,533 --> 00:11:48,666
Look at your husband.

203
00:11:48,966 --> 00:11:50,133
See how possessive he is?

204
00:11:51,700 --> 00:11:53,266
I know you're possessive.

205
00:11:54,066 --> 00:11:55,066
But I forgot to tell you.

206
00:11:55,866 --> 00:11:56,866
My dad knows.

207
00:11:57,566 --> 00:11:59,333
That I broke up with Bom to be with you.

208
00:12:03,566 --> 00:12:04,900
Let's go visit your dad sometime.

209
00:12:08,766 --> 00:12:10,533
Maybe during New Years or Songkran.

210
00:12:10,866 --> 00:12:11,866
We can go back then.

211
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:13,720
He's definitely going to like me.

212
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:16,300
I'm sure of it.

213
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:22,600
Ready, Hia?

214
00:12:23,466 --> 00:12:24,466
Let's do this.

215
00:12:37,333 --> 00:12:38,333
Bom!

216
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:44,333
P'Bom isn't available
to see you right now.

217
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:46,733
And when exactly will he be available?

218
00:12:47,133 --> 00:12:48,133
Until further notice.

219
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:49,966
What, is he on his deathbed?

220
00:12:51,466 --> 00:12:52,466
You guys broke up.

221
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:53,876
Why are you still acting so protective?

222
00:12:53,900 --> 00:12:55,400
I asked you nicely, Ten.

223
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:56,733
You two broke up.

224
00:12:57,100 --> 00:12:58,100
You've already moved on.

225
00:12:58,566 --> 00:13:00,046
Why are you still coming around here?

226
00:13:00,366 --> 00:13:01,686
Then listen to me very carefully.

227
00:13:02,766 --> 00:13:03,866
I'm here to collect a debt.

228
00:13:05,300 --> 00:13:06,400
He took my money.

229
00:13:07,333 --> 00:13:08,333
What money?

230
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:11,220
He ran off with all the money from the bar.

231
00:13:11,466 --> 00:13:12,466
To open his new place.

232
00:13:13,100 --> 00:13:14,733
My dad's money was in there, too.

233
00:13:14,966 --> 00:13:16,700
I just want my dad's share back.

234
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:18,600
As for the rest...

235
00:13:18,733 --> 00:13:20,366
Consider it a donation to a stray dog.

236
00:13:21,533 --> 00:13:22,533
How much?

237
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:24,733
My dad's share is 500,000.

238
00:13:25,666 --> 00:13:27,266
How much does Bom owe you

239
00:13:27,566 --> 00:13:28,566
in total?

240
00:13:28,900 --> 00:13:29,900
Six million in total.

241
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,560
Split down the middle,
that's three million each.

242
00:13:33,333 --> 00:13:34,333
Three million, right?

243
00:13:34,733 --> 00:13:35,800
I'll take care of it.

244
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:39,100
And you, please stay away from P'Bom.

245
00:13:39,933 --> 00:13:41,493
I have no desire to be near him anyway.

246
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:44,133
Just keep your man on a tight leash.

247
00:13:44,733 --> 00:13:46,933
Don't let him come barking around me again.

248
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:50,400
Make sure I get my three million.

249
00:14:16,366 --> 00:14:19,166
Hello, it's A-Ten.

250
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:33,300
Aren't you going to order anything else?

251
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:35,100
Not yet.

252
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:37,400
What's wrong with you?

253
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:40,190
P'Erng and P'In...

254
00:14:40,641 --> 00:14:43,100
They came by, but I
didn't let them see you.

255
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:45,700
P'Erng came to collect his money.

256
00:14:46,666 --> 00:14:47,866
I paid him back in full.

257
00:14:48,500 --> 00:14:49,500
How much?

258
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:50,900
Three million.

259
00:14:56,866 --> 00:14:58,076
I'll find a way to pay you back.

260
00:14:58,100 --> 00:14:59,420
Why won't you just take my money?

261
00:15:01,133 --> 00:15:02,973
Why did you have to take
Erng's money instead?

262
00:15:03,166 --> 00:15:04,266
It's only three million.

263
00:15:04,666 --> 00:15:06,133
You could've just asked me.

264
00:15:07,066 --> 00:15:08,509
I would've given you way more than that.

265
00:15:08,533 --> 00:15:09,533
I know.

266
00:15:10,133 --> 00:15:11,459
I know you would've given me more.

267
00:15:11,460 --> 00:15:12,460
Then why?

268
00:15:13,966 --> 00:15:15,200
Because Erng is Erng.

269
00:15:15,866 --> 00:15:16,666
He's not you.

270
00:15:16,700 --> 00:15:17,820
You love him that much, huh?

271
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:24,540
If we loved each other,
we wouldn't have broken up.

272
00:15:25,966 --> 00:15:27,566
Then why are you trying to win him back?

273
00:15:27,733 --> 00:15:28,733
That's enough, A-Ten.

274
00:15:29,666 --> 00:15:31,200
If you're going to stay, keep quiet.

275
00:15:31,966 --> 00:15:33,006
Stop getting on my nerves.

276
00:15:34,466 --> 00:15:36,186
If being together doesn't make you happy...

277
00:15:36,866 --> 00:15:37,866
Then just end it.

278
00:15:39,266 --> 00:15:40,933
Stop torturing each other like this.

279
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:44,400
Can you at least pretend to love me?

280
00:15:47,266 --> 00:15:48,333
Can you do that?

281
00:15:51,800 --> 00:15:53,000
If I'm miserable,

282
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:55,300
you guys shouldn't
expect to be happy either.

283
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:13,366
Who's going to be a millionaire?
Erng, of course!

284
00:16:13,666 --> 00:16:14,946
Why are you so incredibly happy?

285
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:16,700
I thought you won the lottery.

286
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:17,800
Well...

287
00:16:17,866 --> 00:16:20,266
I got my three million back!

288
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:23,733
Just seeing you happy makes me happy too.

289
00:16:24,133 --> 00:16:26,400
What do you want for dinner? My treat.

290
00:16:26,966 --> 00:16:28,366
How about a 10,000-baht omakase?

291
00:16:29,333 --> 00:16:31,366
But you pay first, and
I'll transfer it to you.

292
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:33,200
No, thanks.

293
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:34,766
I want stirfried seafood.

294
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:36,400
Cooked by you.

295
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:39,142
Come on, Hia. That's way too cheap.

296
00:16:39,143 --> 00:16:40,143
No, it's not.

297
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:41,566
It has sentimental value.

298
00:16:42,333 --> 00:16:43,733
Because my wife is making it.

299
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:47,700
So sweet. Want a 30,000-baht tip?

300
00:16:49,366 --> 00:16:51,800
Look at you getting cocky
now that you have money.

301
00:16:55,266 --> 00:16:58,366
Anyway, where's my shopping list?

302
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:01,600
Right here.

303
00:17:02,366 --> 00:17:04,000
Although I've never run a bar before,

304
00:17:04,366 --> 00:17:06,126
But I used to buy
supplies for temple fairs.

305
00:17:06,166 --> 00:17:08,066
Plastic cups, pitchers, tissues,

306
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:09,666
Extension cords, and rags.

307
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:10,933
It's exactly the same.

308
00:17:11,100 --> 00:17:12,420
I'll buy everything on this list.

309
00:17:12,766 --> 00:17:13,766
Because I'm rich!

310
00:17:14,866 --> 00:17:16,146
Who's going to be a millionaire?

311
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:17,300
Erng!

312
00:17:17,301 --> 00:17:18,541
Of course! Of course!
Of course!

313
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:38,333
Everyone is staring at us, Erng.

314
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:40,760
That's because we're good-looking.

315
00:17:42,700 --> 00:17:45,066
Hia, your hair looks so goddamn cocky.

316
00:17:45,900 --> 00:17:47,000
I like standing out.

317
00:17:47,966 --> 00:17:49,326
I like being the talk of the town.

318
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:51,000
You're weird.

319
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:53,300
You mean cute, right?

320
00:17:54,166 --> 00:17:55,166
Yeah.

321
00:17:56,100 --> 00:17:56,823
You're cute.

322
00:17:56,823 --> 00:17:57,823
Hey.

323
00:17:58,733 --> 00:17:59,866
Are you feeling okay?

324
00:18:00,866 --> 00:18:01,866
Yeah.

325
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:03,400
I'm perfectly fine.

326
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:06,100
You called me cute,

327
00:18:06,933 --> 00:18:08,213
And you're speaking so politely.

328
00:18:08,733 --> 00:18:09,533
Don't tell me...

329
00:18:09,566 --> 00:18:10,666
You're possessed?

330
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:12,733
Do you want to wear my amulet?

331
00:18:12,900 --> 00:18:13,900
Hold on, Hia.

332
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:15,200
I let it slide earlier,

333
00:18:15,666 --> 00:18:17,066
But now you're asking for it.

334
00:18:17,566 --> 00:18:18,886
Let's just get the shopping done.

335
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:25,400
I'll get right on it, boss.

336
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,000
Wait.

337
00:18:30,866 --> 00:18:32,466
Want to have a drinking contest tonight?

338
00:18:34,900 --> 00:18:36,733
First one to throw up loses.

339
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:39,700
I'm in.

340
00:18:40,500 --> 00:18:42,333
I'm not losing to you, Erng.

341
00:18:43,733 --> 00:18:44,733
We'll see about that.

342
00:18:51,133 --> 00:18:52,133
Let's go.

343
00:18:54,866 --> 00:18:55,933
Hia, did you get it?

344
00:18:56,366 --> 00:18:57,366
Got it.

345
00:18:57,900 --> 00:18:58,900
Let's go.

346
00:19:00,366 --> 00:19:01,366
Next stop.

347
00:19:01,997 --> 00:19:02,997
Erng.

348
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:06,600
I got it.

349
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:09,360
Put it in the back so we can head home.

350
00:19:12,766 --> 00:19:14,566
The menu is done. What do you think?

351
00:19:22,733 --> 00:19:23,733
I think it looks great.

352
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:29,160
Beautiful, just like the designer.

353
00:19:31,166 --> 00:19:33,533
We can print and laminate it tomorrow.

354
00:19:34,933 --> 00:19:37,100
We'll put the promo on
a standee by the counter.

355
00:19:39,166 --> 00:19:40,166
Yeah.

356
00:20:02,166 --> 00:20:03,400
That's really spicy.

357
00:20:08,933 --> 00:20:09,933
Hmm?

358
00:20:17,576 --> 00:20:19,013
Give me a cigarette.

359
00:20:33,966 --> 00:20:35,926
We haven't even started
and you're already tipsy?

360
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:40,900
The salad was so spicy,

361
00:20:41,266 --> 00:20:42,746
I had to drink a lot to wash it down.

362
00:20:44,933 --> 00:20:46,053
But I can still take you on.

363
00:20:47,466 --> 00:20:48,506
Whoever throws up first...

364
00:20:49,566 --> 00:20:50,606
Has to clean the bathroom.

365
00:20:51,733 --> 00:20:53,900
I've already laid out the
brush and cleaner for you.

366
00:21:29,966 --> 00:21:31,300
What kind of dance is that?

367
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:33,460
It's my customer-attracting dance.

368
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:34,500
On opening day,

369
00:21:34,566 --> 00:21:36,000
I'm going to dance on the counter.

370
00:22:20,066 --> 00:22:21,800
Did you practice that at a temple?

371
00:22:22,766 --> 00:22:26,700
Spirit houses only get red soda, not beer.

372
00:22:36,750 --> 00:22:37,890
Oops I'm still fine.

373
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:42,320
Where's the water?
[He means beer]

374
00:22:45,269 --> 00:22:46,405
We're out of it, Hia.

375
00:22:53,110 --> 00:22:54,110
Umm.

376
00:23:01,737 --> 00:23:03,510
Oh, look. There's beer.

377
00:23:07,428 --> 00:23:08,797
We still have so much beer.

378
00:23:14,566 --> 00:23:16,933
Hey, Hia, that's enough. Stop drinking.

379
00:23:33,100 --> 00:23:33,900
Hia! Hia!

380
00:23:34,100 --> 00:23:35,100
Are you okay?

381
00:23:39,166 --> 00:23:40,600
You lost to me, Hia.

382
00:24:11,866 --> 00:24:13,148
Are you done?

383
00:24:15,716 --> 00:24:16,716
Where's the brush?

384
00:24:18,951 --> 00:24:20,815
On the second shelf to your left.

385
00:24:29,866 --> 00:24:31,100
What are you smiling at?

386
00:24:32,566 --> 00:24:34,200
I'm smiling at a cute loser.

387
00:24:36,700 --> 00:24:38,260
Make sure you scrub it until it shines,

388
00:24:39,333 --> 00:24:40,366
Mr. Winner.

389
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:43,766
The winner...

390
00:24:44,866 --> 00:24:46,666
will carry the loser back to bed.

391
00:25:04,700 --> 00:25:05,700
Hia?

392
00:25:06,533 --> 00:25:07,533
Hia!

393
00:25:09,800 --> 00:25:10,800
It hurts.

394
00:25:12,866 --> 00:25:14,066
It hurts, Erng.

395
00:25:16,166 --> 00:25:17,200
Where does it hurt?

396
00:25:19,500 --> 00:25:20,500
Right here.

397
00:25:21,984 --> 00:25:22,984
Hia...

398
00:25:23,297 --> 00:25:23,964
Hey!

399
00:25:23,964 --> 00:25:24,964
Erng...

400
00:25:26,036 --> 00:25:27,036
Hia!

401
00:25:28,071 --> 00:25:29,071
Hey!

402
00:25:32,766 --> 00:25:34,300
Get up and talk to me!

403
00:25:38,066 --> 00:25:39,066
Man...

404
00:25:39,466 --> 00:25:41,306
Do I still have to clean
the bathroom tonight?

405
00:25:42,333 --> 00:25:43,333
Yes, you do!

406
00:25:47,400 --> 00:25:48,400
Oh.

407
00:25:56,800 --> 00:25:58,066
Such a lightweight.

408
00:26:11,300 --> 00:26:12,766
Good morning, sunshine.

409
00:26:18,600 --> 00:26:19,600
Your breath stinks.

410
00:26:22,333 --> 00:26:23,333
How are you feeling?

411
00:26:23,966 --> 00:26:24,966
Hungover?

412
00:26:25,266 --> 00:26:26,266
No.

413
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:28,309
I actually feel pretty refreshed right now.

414
00:26:28,333 --> 00:26:29,566
Did I shower last night?

415
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:32,000
I just wiped you down.

416
00:26:33,333 --> 00:26:34,133
And also...

417
00:26:34,333 --> 00:26:36,066
You tried to jump on me last night.

418
00:26:36,400 --> 00:26:37,200
But too bad...

419
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:38,400
You passed out first.

420
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:39,800
Weak.

421
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:42,184
I'm hungry.

422
00:26:42,185 --> 00:26:43,185
Huh?

423
00:26:43,666 --> 00:26:45,026
Why are you hungry so early today?

424
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:47,400
Starving your wife is a sin, you know.

425
00:26:48,133 --> 00:26:50,493
A wife not letting her husband
nibble on her is also a sin.

426
00:26:50,866 --> 00:26:52,766
I haven't nibbled on you for 36 hours.

427
00:26:53,100 --> 00:26:54,266
A whole 36 hours.

428
00:26:54,866 --> 00:26:55,666
Yeah.

429
00:26:55,667 --> 00:26:57,332
Come here and let me freshen you up.

430
00:26:57,333 --> 00:26:58,333
Hey! Whoa!

431
00:26:58,800 --> 00:26:59,800
Come here.

432
00:27:02,333 --> 00:27:03,333
Where are you going?

433
00:27:05,466 --> 00:27:06,266
Hey!

434
00:27:06,333 --> 00:27:07,366
Come on, come here.

435
00:27:07,733 --> 00:27:09,866
Ow! I'm hungry. Hurry!

436
00:27:29,133 --> 00:27:30,133
Hia.

437
00:27:31,070 --> 00:27:32,617
Pay attention to me.

438
00:27:37,800 --> 00:27:41,466
Fine, go ahead and do that.

439
00:27:57,200 --> 00:27:58,266
What are you doing?

440
00:27:59,666 --> 00:28:00,666
Well...

441
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:03,333
I'm arranging the chairs
just like you ordered.

442
00:28:03,766 --> 00:28:04,566
See?

443
00:28:04,733 --> 00:28:06,253
Guaranteed to match your instructions.

444
00:28:06,766 --> 00:28:07,766
Perfectly.

445
00:28:08,700 --> 00:28:10,766
I thought you were going to throw it at me.

446
00:28:15,500 --> 00:28:16,500
Hmph.

447
00:28:16,700 --> 00:28:19,333
Who would dare do that to their wife?

448
00:28:20,500 --> 00:28:21,766
Go cook.

449
00:28:22,533 --> 00:28:23,933
I'll handle things here.

450
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:26,400
Okay.

451
00:28:27,866 --> 00:28:29,026
When you're done with that...

452
00:28:29,866 --> 00:28:31,733
go wash the floor outside.

453
00:28:32,466 --> 00:28:34,400
You might as well water the plants too.

454
00:28:36,300 --> 00:28:37,300
Oh.

455
00:28:38,533 --> 00:28:40,566
Don't forget to wash the motorcycle.

456
00:28:42,800 --> 00:28:44,533
And make sure to put away the hose.

457
00:28:45,166 --> 00:28:46,766
Otherwise, customers might trip over it.

458
00:28:46,866 --> 00:28:49,346
Are you getting back at me for
almost throwing a chair at you?

459
00:28:49,466 --> 00:28:51,866
Just as a husband wouldn't
dare throw a chair at his wife...

460
00:28:52,266 --> 00:28:54,300
a wife can't be bothered
to do all this herself.

461
00:28:55,100 --> 00:28:56,100
That's just great.

462
00:28:59,266 --> 00:29:01,956
My little baby.

463
00:29:03,713 --> 00:29:04,713
Sure.

464
00:30:57,000 --> 00:30:58,566
I've reserved a table for you.

465
00:30:58,966 --> 00:31:01,766
Your text-speak is really annoying.

466
00:31:02,200 --> 00:31:04,166
My deepest, most dramatic apologies.

467
00:31:04,500 --> 00:31:05,666
So, are you free to come?

468
00:31:06,200 --> 00:31:08,533
Yeah, I'm free. Lit is coming too.

469
00:31:09,100 --> 00:31:12,100
As for Aiyaret, he's busy.
I'll answer for him.

470
00:31:12,700 --> 00:31:15,900
I'll be a bit late tonight because
I'm speeding back from Nan.

471
00:31:16,333 --> 00:31:17,333
See you!

472
00:31:19,693 --> 00:31:21,059
Sneaking in a sticker.

473
00:31:21,926 --> 00:31:25,276
I know you just want to show off your new LINE
name matching In's. (I'm in Love with Yai Yayet)

474
00:31:25,300 --> 00:31:27,476
And what on earth is 'Yai Yayet'?
[cute way to say Aiyaret]

475
00:31:27,500 --> 00:31:28,600
Is that Ai's name?

476
00:31:30,066 --> 00:31:31,400
Totally ruined his cool image.

477
00:31:31,666 --> 00:31:34,754
Yeah, my fifth niece
is just learning to talk.

478
00:31:34,755 --> 00:31:35,933
Ai.

479
00:31:35,934 --> 00:31:39,500
I'll send you a clip. The way
she says his name is so cute.

480
00:31:40,166 --> 00:31:41,166
Nai.

481
00:31:41,466 --> 00:31:42,866
You're such a copycat.

482
00:31:43,300 --> 00:31:46,925
Yeah, yeah. My father-in-law
gave me a wad of cash to spend.

483
00:31:46,926 --> 00:31:49,100
I was planning to spend it at your bar.

484
00:31:49,101 --> 00:31:52,266
But since the owner of ChermChey
insulted me like this...

485
00:31:54,066 --> 00:31:55,400
I guess I'll have to reconsider.

486
00:31:55,800 --> 00:31:57,190
In that case, welcome, VIP customer!

487
00:31:57,191 --> 00:32:01,733
A special VIP table where every
menu item is extra expensive!

488
00:32:03,600 --> 00:32:05,266
Damn it, In. I'm done talking to you.

489
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:12,066
What are you doing, Hia?

490
00:32:12,866 --> 00:32:13,866
Food is ready.

491
00:32:14,600 --> 00:32:15,800
Just chatting with my friends.

492
00:32:16,466 --> 00:32:17,466
Let me see.

493
00:32:17,700 --> 00:32:19,533
What did you make?

494
00:32:22,400 --> 00:32:24,866
Bacon fried rice, no veggies.

495
00:32:26,800 --> 00:32:28,666
So, did you reserve a
table for your friends?

496
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:31,200
Yeah.

497
00:32:33,533 --> 00:32:34,800
We already have this sign.

498
00:32:35,300 --> 00:32:36,460
Why didn't you ask the staff?

499
00:32:38,800 --> 00:32:40,400
What time do they get here?

500
00:32:41,333 --> 00:32:42,666
Around four or five, I guess.

501
00:32:43,100 --> 00:32:44,420
But they already know what to do.

502
00:32:44,766 --> 00:32:46,100
No need for a big briefing.

503
00:32:47,200 --> 00:32:48,200
Okay.

504
00:32:49,666 --> 00:32:50,666
Let's eat.

505
00:33:15,100 --> 00:33:16,100
Erng.

506
00:33:18,733 --> 00:33:19,733
Yes?

507
00:33:28,366 --> 00:33:30,007
Go change your pants right now.

508
00:33:30,998 --> 00:33:32,158
I don't have any other pairs.

509
00:33:32,209 --> 00:33:34,209
Come on, you have dozens of clothes.

510
00:33:36,996 --> 00:33:38,070
The others have all been worn.

511
00:33:38,071 --> 00:33:39,999
But this is the only new one.

512
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:41,051
For a grand opening,

513
00:33:41,052 --> 00:33:42,292
the clothes have to be new too.

514
00:33:42,421 --> 00:33:43,421
Oh, please.

515
00:33:43,700 --> 00:33:44,700
Let me see.

516
00:33:45,666 --> 00:33:48,666
Look, it's too tight right here.

517
00:33:50,933 --> 00:33:53,200
See? It's bulging right here.

518
00:33:54,166 --> 00:33:57,066
I don't see any bulge.
Plus, it's comfortable.

519
00:33:57,666 --> 00:33:58,786
I'm tired of talking to you.

520
00:34:00,300 --> 00:34:02,400
I'm just being protective of what's mine.

521
00:34:05,466 --> 00:34:07,281
Erng, where are you going?

522
00:34:07,282 --> 00:34:08,747
To find a new husband!

523
00:34:08,748 --> 00:34:09,726
What about me?

524
00:34:09,726 --> 00:34:10,726
The ex-husband.

525
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:27,300
It doesn't look bulging at all.

526
00:34:41,533 --> 00:34:42,700
Hello, Intha.

527
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:45,166
Your new haircut looks pretty edgy.

528
00:34:45,800 --> 00:34:47,520
Aren't you going to say hi to your friends?

529
00:34:53,166 --> 00:34:54,300
Hi, Tonhon.

530
00:34:55,333 --> 00:34:56,400
Hi, Chonlathi.

531
00:34:56,866 --> 00:34:57,966
Your table is inside.

532
00:34:59,066 --> 00:35:00,426
I need to go make up with my wife.

533
00:35:00,966 --> 00:35:01,966
We just fought.

534
00:35:02,166 --> 00:35:03,166
Wait.

535
00:35:03,800 --> 00:35:04,966
Take these prawns with you.

536
00:35:05,700 --> 00:35:07,333
Make something delicious for me.

537
00:35:08,766 --> 00:35:09,766
Wow.

538
00:35:10,800 --> 00:35:11,800
My dear friend...

539
00:35:12,166 --> 00:35:13,766
putting me to work
the moment you arrive.

540
00:35:13,933 --> 00:35:16,500
Well, when I arrived, you were
leaving to appease your wife.

541
00:35:18,933 --> 00:35:20,093
The place is fully decorated.

542
00:35:21,012 --> 00:35:22,012
It looks nice.

543
00:35:22,686 --> 00:35:25,066
Congratulations. I hope
your business does great.

544
00:35:25,966 --> 00:35:27,466
Congratulations to you too, P'In.

545
00:35:31,300 --> 00:35:32,940
Aren't we going to the convenience store?

546
00:35:33,466 --> 00:35:34,566
You said you wanted snacks.

547
00:35:35,866 --> 00:35:38,666
Oh, right. I almost forgot.

548
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:40,680
We'll head to the convenience store first.

549
00:35:40,900 --> 00:35:42,660
Don't forget to make
me something delicious.

550
00:35:42,966 --> 00:35:44,366
Then hurry back.

551
00:35:47,790 --> 00:35:49,294
What was that about?

552
00:35:50,375 --> 00:35:51,375
Just...

553
00:35:52,700 --> 00:35:53,700
congratulating him.

554
00:36:08,900 --> 00:36:11,500
Oh, Hia In, do you need help carrying that?

555
00:36:12,266 --> 00:36:13,596
It's okay.

556
00:36:14,136 --> 00:36:15,136
I'll carry it myself.

557
00:36:16,285 --> 00:36:18,470
Is Erng still in the kitchen?

558
00:36:18,533 --> 00:36:19,880
Yes, he is.

559
00:36:19,881 --> 00:36:23,066
Oh, and P'Erng asked me to tell you
to meet him in the kitchen.

560
00:36:24,933 --> 00:36:26,300
Okay, thanks a lot.

561
00:36:28,166 --> 00:36:29,766
Take good care of the customers tonight.

562
00:36:30,366 --> 00:36:31,366
Understood.

563
00:36:47,300 --> 00:36:48,027
Erng.

564
00:36:48,027 --> 00:36:49,027
Hey.

565
00:36:50,266 --> 00:36:51,733
Ton and the guys brought these.

566
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:54,080
What can we make with them?

567
00:36:55,300 --> 00:36:56,740
We should grill them, right, Auntie?

568
00:36:57,566 --> 00:36:58,566
Sure.

569
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:00,000
Here you go.

570
00:37:01,100 --> 00:37:03,066
I'll make my special dipping sauce for you.

571
00:37:03,533 --> 00:37:05,333
Your cooking is the absolute best.

572
00:37:05,700 --> 00:37:07,376
Customers keep coming back because of you.

573
00:37:07,400 --> 00:37:09,133
Oh, you're too sweet, Mr. Erng.

574
00:37:09,766 --> 00:37:10,766
I mean it.

575
00:37:11,100 --> 00:37:12,066
I'll leave it to you, Auntie.

576
00:37:12,066 --> 00:37:13,066
Okay.

577
00:37:14,300 --> 00:37:16,900
Auntie, I'm going to
step outside for a bit.

578
00:37:17,066 --> 00:37:17,666
Sure.

579
00:37:17,667 --> 00:37:20,200
Come on, let's take a
photo with the shop sign.

580
00:37:20,201 --> 00:37:21,500
I want to post it on our page.

581
00:37:21,666 --> 00:37:22,866
Are you not mad at me anymore?

582
00:37:24,466 --> 00:37:27,266
Hmph, I'm still mad.

583
00:37:29,200 --> 00:37:30,299
Let's go take a photo.

584
00:37:30,300 --> 00:37:31,300
Hey.

585
00:37:31,933 --> 00:37:32,933
Hurry up.

586
00:37:33,066 --> 00:37:34,066
Whoa.

587
00:37:53,100 --> 00:37:54,230
Please stop being mad at me.

588
00:37:54,472 --> 00:37:57,072
"Please stop being mad."

589
00:37:57,807 --> 00:37:58,807
Please?

590
00:37:59,766 --> 00:38:00,800
Stop being mad at me.

591
00:38:01,926 --> 00:38:03,081
Fine, fine.

592
00:38:03,622 --> 00:38:04,622
I'll stop.

593
00:38:05,217 --> 00:38:07,217
Let's take a selfie.

594
00:38:11,066 --> 00:38:12,066
Hold on.

595
00:38:15,999 --> 00:38:17,821
One, two...

596
00:38:33,933 --> 00:38:35,200
What should the caption be?

597
00:38:35,933 --> 00:38:37,253
I don't know about the caption...

598
00:38:37,715 --> 00:38:39,242
but pork cracklings for sure!
[pork cracklings sounds like "caption"]

599
00:38:39,266 --> 00:38:40,666
Yeah, think of a good one.

600
00:38:41,900 --> 00:38:42,900
Hurry.

601
00:38:44,133 --> 00:38:45,133
Yeah.

602
00:38:45,844 --> 00:38:47,744
ChermChey is now open!

603
00:38:48,333 --> 00:38:49,333
Excellent.

604
00:38:49,966 --> 00:38:51,333
ChermChey is ready to serve you.

605
00:38:53,766 --> 00:38:54,766
ChermChey

606
00:38:55,700 --> 00:38:57,500
is now open!

607
00:38:59,646 --> 00:39:01,646
(ChermChey is now open!)

608
00:39:04,966 --> 00:39:06,066
Let's get started.

609
00:39:07,100 --> 00:39:08,100
Erng, Erng.

610
00:39:09,466 --> 00:39:10,466
Yeah?

611
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:13,066
Love this place a lot,

612
00:39:15,133 --> 00:39:16,600
and don't forget to love me too.

613
00:39:28,366 --> 00:39:29,366
Be good.

614
00:39:33,166 --> 00:39:34,400
Come on, let's go inside.

615
00:40:03,266 --> 00:40:04,906
The bar next door is playing great music.

616
00:41:31,966 --> 00:41:33,266
Do you like it like this?

617
00:41:44,729 --> 00:41:45,918
I do.

618
00:41:52,906 --> 00:41:53,915
Intha &amp; Akara.

619
00:41:55,566 --> 00:41:59,333
My life right now is in full-on
"husband and wife building a life" mode.

620
00:41:59,900 --> 00:42:01,266
Buying supplies during the day,

621
00:42:02,066 --> 00:42:03,786
competing to see who gets drunker at night.

622
00:42:03,966 --> 00:42:06,446
At 3:00 AM, I almost had to
stitch up my boyfriend's forehead.

623
00:42:06,766 --> 00:42:10,766
But the good thing about being drunk is
having Erng take care of me. It's worth it.

624
00:42:11,500 --> 00:42:14,802
I only just realized that
when Hia gets drunk,

625
00:42:14,803 --> 00:42:16,688
he's like a big old dog.

626
00:42:17,544 --> 00:42:21,400
Acting tough, being clingy,
and babbling endlessly.

627
00:42:23,000 --> 00:42:25,378
Since I met Erng, I
really laugh a lot more.

628
00:42:25,693 --> 00:42:29,917
Even though I get scolded, put
to work, and kicked off the bed,

629
00:42:30,225 --> 00:42:31,931
I'm still so happy.

630
00:42:32,966 --> 00:42:35,933
Even if sometimes I feel like
I'm just an employee here.

631
00:42:36,966 --> 00:42:38,501
I never used to think

632
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:43,196
that I'd be sitting here looking
at my own bar with someone.

633
00:42:45,313 --> 00:42:47,026
I only ever thought about

634
00:42:47,747 --> 00:42:48,747
making money,

635
00:42:49,783 --> 00:42:51,442
surviving,

636
00:42:52,933 --> 00:42:54,853
and just getting through
another exhausting day.

637
00:42:57,800 --> 00:42:59,700
But now, things are truly different.

638
00:43:07,066 --> 00:43:08,766
I know Erng has been through a lot.

639
00:43:09,333 --> 00:43:10,133
With the bar,

640
00:43:10,266 --> 00:43:11,066
the money,

641
00:43:11,166 --> 00:43:12,166
and Bom.

642
00:43:15,500 --> 00:43:17,264
So he doesn't really believe that happiness

643
00:43:17,265 --> 00:43:18,870
will last very long for him.

644
00:43:20,222 --> 00:43:23,716
I'll prove to him that this
time, it won't fall apart.

645
00:43:28,600 --> 00:43:30,533
I don't know what the future holds,

646
00:43:31,766 --> 00:43:33,133
if the bar will survive,

647
00:43:34,400 --> 00:43:35,666
if we'll have enough money,

648
00:43:38,500 --> 00:43:40,566
or when trouble will find us again.

649
00:43:46,133 --> 00:43:50,166
But right now, having Hia by my side

650
00:43:58,100 --> 00:43:59,800
is honestly more than enough.

651
00:44:03,566 --> 00:44:05,126
(Next Episode)
Let this place be a home.

652
00:44:05,366 --> 00:44:06,366
Our home.

653
00:44:07,466 --> 00:44:09,766
May this place always be
filled with joy and warmth.

654
00:44:13,400 --> 00:44:17,500
I made this for you so you won't lose it.

655
00:44:19,533 --> 00:44:21,693
A Phra Khun Phaen amulet.
[A famous amulet]

656
00:44:22,000 --> 00:44:23,280
This version is super charming.

657
00:44:23,366 --> 00:44:24,366
Boom!

658
00:44:25,733 --> 00:44:26,800
This is my turn.

659
00:44:26,966 --> 00:44:28,166
I won't let you kiss me.

660
00:44:31,066 --> 00:44:31,866
Hey!

661
00:44:31,966 --> 00:44:33,006
Hia, where are the snacks?

662
00:44:33,100 --> 00:44:33,900
One more time.

663
00:44:34,100 --> 00:44:35,333
Hia! Mr. Erng!

664
00:44:35,366 --> 00:44:37,086
Customers are fighting in front of the bar!

665
00:44:37,700 --> 00:44:38,900
Drag them out of the bar!

666
00:44:39,266 --> 00:44:40,266
Damn it!

667
00:44:41,900 --> 00:44:43,340
I don't welcome customers like this.

668
00:44:43,800 --> 00:44:44,800
I think

669
00:44:45,845 --> 00:44:47,845
they're trying to trash
the place, not just fight.

670
00:44:56,000 --> 00:44:57,000
Who hired you?

671
00:44:57,500 --> 00:44:58,500
Answer me!
